    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>I am unable to get this working with the javac compiler, and I get the same error.</p>\n\n<blockquote>\n  <p>Error:(9, 14) java: package lombok does not exist</p>\n</blockquote>\n\n<p>I have enabled annotation processor, and have also tried rebuilding the project, invalidate cache/restart. Doesn't help.</p>\n\n<p>I did however get it to work partially with eclipse compiler. I say partial because although the build passes successfully, the editor still complains about \"Cannot resolve symbol\".</p>\n\n<p>Idea - 15.04 community edition\nLombok - 1.16.6\nLombok plugin (<a href=\"https://github.com/mplushnikov/lombok-intellij-plugin\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://github.com/mplushnikov/lombok-intellij-plugin</a>) - 0.9.8\nJDK - 1.8.0_51</p>\n\n<p>Update:\nOk, I finally got this working. Mine was a gradle project, and lombok was configured as a custom \"provided\" configuration. Worked fine after adding this in build.gradle</p>\n\n<pre><code>idea {\n module {\n     scopes.PROVIDED.plus += [configurations.provided]\n    }\n}\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>So, 3 steps</p>\n\n<ol>\n<li>Install Lombok plugin from File->Settings->Plugins</li>\n<li>Enable Annotation Processor (javac compiler works too)</li>\n<li>Ensure that you have build.gradle or pom.xml updated for idea if you are adding lombok as a custom config.</li>\n</ol>\n"
  }, {
